WEBVTT

00:05.614 --> 00:07.268
Welcome to Moonhaven.

00:07.398 --> 00:09.835
We've waited a long time
for this moment.

00:09.966 --> 00:14.275
With the assistance of IO,
the technology to save our world

00:14.405 --> 00:15.406
is coming.

00:15.537 --> 00:17.147
Why did you bring me here?

00:17.278 --> 00:19.497
There hasn't been a murder here
in a long time.

00:19.628 --> 00:22.674
You will destabilize everything
just to stay in power?

00:22.805 --> 00:24.198
Woman:
Only if you compel me.

00:24.328 --> 00:26.678
There may be an agent here
from Earth

00:26.809 --> 00:28.028
trying to destroy everything.

00:28.158 --> 00:30.073
Bella:
How do you know it's not me?

00:30.204 --> 00:32.249
I don't.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.904
They lied to us.
The Bridge is a trap.

00:37.863 --> 00:40.997
[engine roars]

00:41.041 --> 00:44.000
[ominous music]

00:44.044 --> 00:50.920
♪

00:58.406 --> 01:00.234
- Congratulations.

01:00.277 --> 01:03.150
If you made it here,
it means you're special.

01:03.193 --> 01:06.196
♪

01:06.240 --> 01:08.242
[indistinct chatter]
- Move along, please.

01:08.285 --> 01:09.895
- [sighs]
- Single file.

01:09.939 --> 01:12.289
- You will train here
in machine language,

01:12.333 --> 01:14.857
ciphers, and system analyses

01:14.900 --> 01:18.078
to see who has the talent
and, indeed, the grit

01:18.121 --> 01:19.905
to help address
the most pressing issues

01:19.949 --> 01:20.993
of our day.

01:24.258 --> 01:27.435
Some of you will not make it
past the week.

01:27.478 --> 01:30.351
Some will go on to build
the radical new technologies

01:30.394 --> 01:33.180
that IO conceives
for humanity's survival.

01:33.223 --> 01:37.836
♪

01:37.880 --> 01:39.708
Perhaps someday,

01:39.751 --> 01:42.145
one of you will be chosen
as Envoy

01:42.189 --> 01:45.148
and help usher in the Bridge.

01:45.279 --> 01:47.368
Your Thimble will be
your main interface

01:47.498 --> 01:49.370
with the IO simulator

01:49.500 --> 01:51.023
and your primary tool
for learning

01:51.154 --> 01:54.114
the various processes
and inner workings

01:54.244 --> 01:57.682
of the most sophisticated
computer matrix ever built.

01:59.380 --> 02:01.947
[display screens beeping]
Learn well.

02:02.078 --> 02:06.474
And remember,
the future is better.

02:06.517 --> 02:07.866
- Speak your name.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.999
- Indira Mare.

02:16.527 --> 02:19.661
- I can't do this without you.

02:23.447 --> 02:26.407
[dramatic music]

02:26.450 --> 02:33.196
♪

03:10.233 --> 03:13.105
[birds chirping]

03:25.944 --> 03:28.469
- Arlo.

03:28.599 --> 03:32.473
Wake up, you old bag of bones.

03:50.578 --> 03:52.710
- So darkness comes,

03:52.841 --> 03:55.409
and we are never going to save
the Earth.

03:55.539 --> 03:58.629
It was all lies.

03:58.760 --> 04:01.110
And you woke me for this?

04:04.287 --> 04:07.029
[laughs]

04:07.159 --> 04:09.118
- If you'd have seen her face,
you'd have woke me.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.163
- Mm-mm.
- It was terrifying, Arlo.

04:11.294 --> 04:13.905
I had to walk the woods
just to lose my tremble.

04:14.036 --> 04:16.168
- So you believe what she says.

04:16.299 --> 04:18.083
- I believe she believed it.

04:18.214 --> 04:19.520
Whatever Chill and Strego
were into,

04:19.650 --> 04:21.522
it soaked their minds.

04:21.652 --> 04:23.698
- And this message
Chill left behind

04:23.828 --> 04:25.613
was meant
for her water sister Asus?

04:25.743 --> 04:27.963
- She wanted Asus to know
that they'd done something.

04:28.093 --> 04:30.139
Felt like a warning.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.227
- But if they're
together in this,

04:31.358 --> 04:33.011
why would he kill her?

04:35.579 --> 04:36.972
- Maybe she had
a change a heart.

04:37.102 --> 04:39.757
- So he comforted her
with a rock to the head.

04:39.888 --> 04:42.107
- Look, if they thought
the Bridge was a lie

04:42.238 --> 04:43.457
and were trying to do
something to stop it,

04:43.587 --> 04:44.936
that would be a secret
worth keeping.

04:45.067 --> 04:46.677
- Paul,

04:46.808 --> 04:50.290
Chill's words were
nogginswirl and buzz.

04:50.420 --> 04:52.988
Let the sunwarm
calm your craze.

04:53.118 --> 04:56.252
We will find the truth.

04:56.383 --> 04:59.299
And I must speak this
to you now:

04:59.429 --> 05:01.170
I will nap at lunch today.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.086
- [chuckles]

05:04.216 --> 05:06.044
Grats, meega.
- Mm.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.048
You make bad tea.

05:10.179 --> 05:13.095
[birds chirping]

05:17.099 --> 05:18.100
- How now?

05:18.230 --> 05:20.363
- I'm Blu.
Your 'prentice.

05:30.155 --> 05:33.071
[melancholy music]

05:33.115 --> 05:39.948
♪

06:30.302 --> 06:33.262
[hologram buzzes]

06:33.305 --> 06:35.220
- In these last few moments,

06:35.264 --> 06:37.179
I have felt closer to you

06:37.222 --> 06:39.964
than I ever have
another living soul.

06:40.008 --> 06:41.749
I look at you, sharp heart,

06:41.792 --> 06:44.186
and I know my path is true.

06:44.229 --> 06:46.971
If you do not see me
by your side,

06:47.015 --> 06:48.886
I am with you.

06:48.930 --> 06:53.630
If you do not hear my voice,
I am with you.

06:53.674 --> 06:56.807
My absence, love,
is proof of nothing.

06:59.506 --> 07:01.377
- Bella.

07:06.948 --> 07:07.862
What are you doing out here?

07:11.039 --> 07:12.693
The voice.

07:12.823 --> 07:14.651
- A letter to my sister.

07:17.959 --> 07:19.874
- Want to talk about it?

07:20.004 --> 07:23.312
- I can't tell you how much
I don't want to talk about it.

07:26.576 --> 07:29.144
- I have a secret.

07:29.274 --> 07:32.103
I found it.

07:32.234 --> 07:34.062
[twigs crunch]

07:34.192 --> 07:36.499
[bird calls distantly]

07:36.630 --> 07:38.240
- Somebody's out there.

07:38.283 --> 07:40.677
[mysterious music]

07:40.808 --> 07:42.374
They've been watching me.

07:42.418 --> 07:47.728
♪

07:47.858 --> 07:51.688
- Are Earth forests enchanted?

07:51.819 --> 07:54.778
I've read stories,
but Doda says

07:54.909 --> 07:56.998
there's no magic here.

07:57.128 --> 07:59.870
He says they left it all
behind on Earth

08:00.001 --> 08:02.656
so we could think clearly.

08:09.619 --> 08:11.708
- I've been given
an apprentice.

08:11.839 --> 08:13.971
- Are they gonna creep
like that the whole time?

08:14.102 --> 08:15.712
- They watch and learn.

08:15.843 --> 08:17.322
So what did you see?

08:17.453 --> 08:18.628
- I heard them.

08:18.759 --> 08:21.196
Someone's been following me.
- Who?

08:21.326 --> 08:24.242
- I don't want
to endanger your family, Paul.

08:24.373 --> 08:26.070
Tomm tried to kill me
because I saw something

08:26.201 --> 08:27.594
he didn't want me to see.

08:27.724 --> 08:29.944
- Tomm isn't any danger now.

08:30.074 --> 08:32.729
- I think Chill and Strego
were working for him.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.775
If they were radicalized,
there might be others.

08:34.905 --> 08:36.124
- Radicalized?

08:36.254 --> 08:38.953
- Strego cut out
his own Mark, Paul.

08:39.083 --> 08:40.824
What would make
a Mooner do that?

08:40.955 --> 08:42.565
- Regret?

08:42.696 --> 08:44.567
He wasn't joining something,
he was leaving it,

08:44.698 --> 08:46.656
leaving us.

08:46.787 --> 08:48.963
- Or dropping off the grid
to plant a bomb

08:49.093 --> 08:51.487
or poison the water.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.402
I need to see the Envoy.

08:53.533 --> 08:55.317
She needs to hear
what happened on CAT.

08:55.447 --> 08:58.450
- Is it safe?
- Hmm.

08:58.581 --> 09:00.452
I guess I'll find out.

09:09.026 --> 09:11.986
[insects buzzing]

09:12.029 --> 09:14.945
[eerie music]

09:14.989 --> 09:21.909
♪

09:23.911 --> 09:25.652
- My pilot returns.

09:27.915 --> 09:29.351
Do you have any answers?

09:31.527 --> 09:33.921
They don't believe
in fate here.

09:34.051 --> 09:36.837
No gods either.

09:36.967 --> 09:39.317
If there's an unseen force,

09:39.448 --> 09:42.016
it's just our own noise
and music

09:42.146 --> 09:45.672
drawing us
into unexplored rooms.

09:45.802 --> 09:48.109
- Is the coincidence
keeping you up at night?

09:49.980 --> 09:53.070
Me? My sister's murder?

09:53.201 --> 09:56.073
Slotting into your loop
at the last minute?

09:56.204 --> 09:57.814
- It's crossed my mind.

10:00.469 --> 10:03.733
Why did you come to Moonhaven?

10:03.864 --> 10:07.694
- I came for the smuggling,
stayed for the people.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.915
I'm not the Earth agent
sent to disrupt the Bridge,

10:12.046 --> 10:14.962
but someone's
turning Mooners against it,

10:15.092 --> 10:16.964
spreading rumors.

10:17.094 --> 10:20.489
- There are always threats,
but the work continues.

10:20.620 --> 10:22.317
The transport ships
that land today

10:22.447 --> 10:25.320
will take the First Wave
back to Earth.

10:25.450 --> 10:27.409
The Bridge is safe.

10:27.539 --> 10:30.499
- I was trained to lie,
so take this as you want.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.676
Tomm is half blind
and barely alive

10:33.807 --> 10:36.244
because he tried to kill me.

10:36.374 --> 10:40.117
Your bodyguard is
a double agent.

10:40.248 --> 10:44.556
- Tomm loves Moonhaven
more than the Earth.

10:44.687 --> 10:46.950
He believes
in what we're doing.

10:47.081 --> 10:49.126
He would never betray me.

10:49.257 --> 10:51.172
- He has.

10:51.302 --> 10:52.303
And you either
know that already

10:52.434 --> 10:53.565
or you don't.

10:53.696 --> 10:57.395
But I wanted you to hear it
from me.

10:57.526 --> 10:59.310
- Why?

10:59.441 --> 11:02.226
- Figured I'd learn something
either way.

11:02.270 --> 11:08.711
♪

11:09.886 --> 11:12.759
[subdued music]

11:12.802 --> 11:19.722
♪

11:25.032 --> 11:27.382
[display beeping]

11:39.307 --> 11:40.569
- Where you from?

11:40.700 --> 11:43.528
- Um, Heinlein Park.
Near Pittsburg?

11:43.659 --> 11:46.444
- Wow, a ration country.
Must be rough.

11:46.575 --> 11:49.883
- The people are good.
They just don't have much.

11:50.013 --> 11:51.406
I lost my parents.

11:51.536 --> 11:53.364
but it was early on,
so, you know...

11:53.495 --> 11:55.627
- Yeah. Sorry.

11:55.758 --> 11:58.195
- I made it here.
What about you?

11:58.326 --> 12:00.676
- New Brompton,
outside of London.

12:00.807 --> 12:04.985
The people suck.
We're just rich.

12:05.115 --> 12:06.987
- Do you ever get homesick?

12:07.117 --> 12:08.728
- Not much to miss back home.

12:08.858 --> 12:11.513
My brothers fought
in the Water Wars.

12:11.643 --> 12:14.734
One of them came back...
different.

12:14.864 --> 12:18.172
The other one,
you know, didn't.

12:18.302 --> 12:19.913
Kinda tore my family apart.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.655
But we're survivors, right?

12:23.699 --> 12:26.658
[dramatic music]

12:26.702 --> 12:33.622
♪

12:38.627 --> 12:41.499
[birds chirping]

12:47.201 --> 12:50.291
- Grats, kid.
You found her.

12:50.421 --> 12:54.469
- They'll see you.
- Nah, I got tricks.

12:54.599 --> 12:56.819
You should go home.

13:00.823 --> 13:03.695
[grate squeaks]

13:18.145 --> 13:21.235
[display beeping]

13:21.278 --> 13:22.236
[alarm blaring]

13:22.366 --> 13:23.715
[sighs]

13:37.729 --> 13:40.689
[tense music]

13:40.732 --> 13:47.609
♪

13:50.917 --> 13:53.354
The Singer was delivered to me
in this.

13:55.225 --> 13:57.314
- You went back to your ship?

13:57.445 --> 14:01.101
- CAT's not going anywhere.
I need parts.

14:01.231 --> 14:02.972
- Hmm.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.931
- You said the Singer was
a big deal.

14:05.061 --> 14:07.324
Whoever wanted it down on Earth
had to connect

14:07.455 --> 14:08.369
with a Mooner up here.

14:08.499 --> 14:09.805
- Down here.

14:11.372 --> 14:13.853
Up there.

14:13.983 --> 14:16.290
- I thought
they weren't allowed to talk.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.901
- Yeah.
- [scoffs]

14:19.032 --> 14:21.861
If Tomm was recruiting locals
to resist the Earth,

14:21.991 --> 14:24.341
maybe one of them was willing
to help smuggle drugs.

14:24.472 --> 14:27.823
- This box has no markings,
no trade scratch.

14:27.954 --> 14:31.740
- I watched a pelican dissolve
and leave it behind.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.394
Does that make it easier?

14:39.704 --> 14:42.838
[electronics buzzing]

14:44.144 --> 14:46.059
- Whoever made that box
will be in this room.

14:50.541 --> 14:51.847
[bird caws]

14:53.762 --> 14:55.242
Indira's asked
for extra security

14:55.372 --> 14:57.766
for her bodyguard.
Arlo's volunteered.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.376
He's had some experience
bringing people out the Singer.

14:59.507 --> 15:00.812
It can be tricky.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.640
- He should have protection.

15:02.771 --> 15:05.034
If Tomm starts talking,
he'll be a liability.

15:05.165 --> 15:07.210
- From who?
- Anyone else involved.

15:07.341 --> 15:09.778
- If there is
anyone else involved.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.171
- [scoffs]

15:15.088 --> 15:16.524
Paul.

15:23.792 --> 15:26.360
[suspenseful music]

15:26.490 --> 15:28.057
- Bella.
both: Sirl?

15:28.188 --> 15:30.755
- Bella, don't go in there!
Stop!

15:30.886 --> 15:32.801
You, wait there.

15:32.844 --> 15:39.503
♪

16:00.655 --> 16:03.527
[soft mysterious music]

16:03.571 --> 16:10.491
♪

16:19.239 --> 16:20.544
- [gasps]

16:20.588 --> 16:27.551
♪

16:29.031 --> 16:31.860
[baby crying]

16:35.298 --> 16:36.865
Ah!

16:36.908 --> 16:39.563
[baby crying]

16:39.607 --> 16:46.396
♪

17:00.628 --> 17:03.587
[baby gurgling]

17:03.631 --> 17:10.594
♪

17:31.441 --> 17:32.790
- Bella.

17:36.272 --> 17:38.666
- What the fuck is this place?

17:42.104 --> 17:44.150
[flames whoosh]

17:44.280 --> 17:46.021
He got away.

17:51.592 --> 17:52.506
- Are you all right?

17:59.730 --> 18:01.297
This is Mirrorwell.

18:01.428 --> 18:03.343
A Dreamer circle built it.

18:03.473 --> 18:05.084
- Why?

18:05.214 --> 18:06.433
- It's supposed to stretch you
in places

18:06.563 --> 18:07.912
you don't want to be stretched.

18:08.043 --> 18:09.218
- That's sick.

18:09.349 --> 18:11.829
- It's useful
if you're prepared.

18:11.960 --> 18:14.876
- [weeping]

18:19.359 --> 18:20.882
I had nothing to do
with stealing the drug.

18:21.012 --> 18:23.014
- This isn't about drugs, Sirl.

18:23.145 --> 18:26.235
Your paradise may be
under attack.

18:26.366 --> 18:29.151
If you're in too deep,
we can help you out.

18:29.282 --> 18:30.500
But you gotta talk.

18:30.631 --> 18:33.721
- [chuckles]

18:33.851 --> 18:36.724
I saw you in the Mirrorwell.

18:36.854 --> 18:40.467
You were not so strong there.

18:40.597 --> 18:43.992
I see the pain you carry
behind your eyes.

18:44.123 --> 18:45.863
- There's none behind yours?

18:45.994 --> 18:47.952
- [groans]
- How 'bout now?

18:48.083 --> 18:51.217
- Control your violence.
- That was controlled.

18:51.347 --> 18:53.219
Who asked you to make this?

18:53.349 --> 18:54.394
Who's the Earth agent?

18:54.524 --> 18:57.614
- I never met an Earther
till you.

18:57.745 --> 18:59.834
Is this what awaits
the First Wave?

18:59.964 --> 19:03.229
Bonecrack and bloodspill?

19:03.359 --> 19:06.057
Been bred into you for so long,
how will you ever unlearn it?

19:06.188 --> 19:08.147
- Right.

19:08.277 --> 19:10.061
So why not pull up
the drawbridge here

19:10.192 --> 19:12.020
and keep all the toys
for yourselves?

19:12.151 --> 19:14.196
And why fix
hunger and thirst on Earth

19:14.327 --> 19:15.937
when you can
just send them drugs

19:16.067 --> 19:18.287
and watch them
burn themselves out?

19:18.418 --> 19:19.636
- Bella, stop.
- Me?

19:19.767 --> 19:21.377
- No Mooner
would think this way.

19:21.508 --> 19:23.771
- I think some would, Paul.

19:23.901 --> 19:25.729
And I think he's one of them.

19:25.860 --> 19:27.340
And soon we're gonna know,

19:27.470 --> 19:30.560
because I saw
the Envoy's guard this morning,

19:30.691 --> 19:32.780
and he's waking up.

19:32.910 --> 19:35.174
He's gonna be talking soon.

19:35.304 --> 19:37.437
And then there's gonna be
no more secrets.

19:41.745 --> 19:43.094
- I have nothing to tell you.

19:45.227 --> 19:47.447
- Sirl.

19:47.577 --> 19:48.883
- Let him go.

19:58.806 --> 20:00.242
- Hey, why didn't you tell me
Tomm had woke?

20:00.373 --> 20:01.461
- Because he didn't.

20:01.591 --> 20:03.027
But if Sirl thinks
he's talking,

20:03.158 --> 20:05.769
he'll want to warn
whoever else is involved.

20:05.900 --> 20:06.988
- How will we know?

20:07.118 --> 20:08.294
- He's Marked, right?

20:08.424 --> 20:09.947
Use your machine to track him.

20:10.078 --> 20:11.732
- IO doesn't work like that.

20:11.862 --> 20:12.776
We can track people
if there's been

20:12.907 --> 20:13.995
an injury or death,

20:14.125 --> 20:15.170
but it's not for surveillance.

20:15.301 --> 20:16.737
- Jesus.

20:16.867 --> 20:18.695
Would a little bit of dystopia
kill you guys?

20:18.826 --> 20:21.176
- I'll find him.

20:21.307 --> 20:23.091
I'll follow and tell you
where he goes.

20:25.833 --> 20:27.443
- You can't send a kid.

20:28.966 --> 20:30.664
- Stay far behind.

20:30.794 --> 20:32.100
Don't let him see you.

20:37.323 --> 20:39.977
We learn by doing.

20:40.108 --> 20:41.240
- Who makes the Singer?
Is it IO?

20:41.370 --> 20:42.806
- No, it's people.

20:42.937 --> 20:45.026
People who can be trusted.
I'll take you.

20:51.337 --> 20:55.428
- Among the most complex
of the New Fauna

20:55.471 --> 20:58.082
is the Radix Tenebris.

20:58.213 --> 21:00.737
Say, what makes it unique?

21:00.868 --> 21:03.436
Ori?
- The polymorphous nano-zime.

21:03.566 --> 21:05.002
- Without which
we would never feel

21:05.133 --> 21:08.441
the smooth-cool of the Bright

21:08.571 --> 21:10.965
or the thrill-pound of Openeye.

21:11.095 --> 21:14.142
You are all mechanics
of the Unseen.

21:14.185 --> 21:16.057
[gentle music]

21:16.187 --> 21:18.189
In our work,
we seek connection.

21:18.320 --> 21:19.974
We are built-things
in the world,

21:20.104 --> 21:23.673
but we also exist as thoughts
in those who love us.

21:23.804 --> 21:26.981
Our heart is here.

21:27.111 --> 21:31.333
But our soul is in our friends.

21:31.377 --> 21:36.512
♪

21:36.643 --> 21:39.210
- Your Second said
you may have some time for us.

21:39.341 --> 21:41.822
- Thank you, Sonda.

21:41.952 --> 21:44.868
The smuggler heals her wound
by helping you, 'tective.

21:46.653 --> 21:48.524
- She sees where I am blind.

21:48.655 --> 21:50.221
- You are brave, Bella.

21:51.745 --> 21:52.789
For many Mooners,

21:52.920 --> 21:55.749
you are the Mother Planet
made real.

21:55.879 --> 21:57.925
- Sorry for your sister.

21:58.055 --> 21:59.883
- Did you know Chill?

22:00.014 --> 22:02.059
- We never crossed,

22:02.190 --> 22:05.193
but I feel her loss.

22:05.324 --> 22:06.890
- How can we help?

22:07.021 --> 22:08.979
- You make the Singer here?

22:09.110 --> 22:11.808
- We ask because--
- Because it was stolen.

22:11.939 --> 22:13.419
- It's never happened before.

22:13.549 --> 22:14.594
- I hate to tell you,

22:14.724 --> 22:16.813
but smuggling Moonstuff's
not new.

22:16.944 --> 22:19.599
I never loot drugs,
but rocks, knickknacks.

22:19.729 --> 22:21.514
I got paid once
to bring a full cargo hold

22:21.644 --> 22:23.254
of seawater home.

22:23.385 --> 22:25.300
They sold it like it was holy.

22:25.431 --> 22:26.910
But the Singer was different.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.869
They wanted to copy it,
make it on Earth.

22:28.999 --> 22:31.828
- The Singer serves one purpose
on Moonhaven,

22:31.959 --> 22:33.874
our midlife celebration.

22:34.004 --> 22:36.006
- But no Mooner would steal it.

22:36.137 --> 22:37.704
- How can you all be so sure?

22:37.834 --> 22:40.968
- Because we understand
something you cannot.

22:43.100 --> 22:45.755
- Truelune.
- [scoffs]

22:45.886 --> 22:47.670
- Truelune is trust.

22:47.801 --> 22:51.805
It means we trust each other
to do what is right for all.

22:53.807 --> 22:56.375
To do what is right
for the future.

22:59.247 --> 23:00.901
The future is better.

23:00.944 --> 23:03.947
[soft tense music]

23:03.991 --> 23:10.911
♪

23:16.830 --> 23:18.309
- Something on your mind?

23:18.440 --> 23:21.704
Besides how weird that was?

23:21.835 --> 23:23.924
- You know what's on my mind.

23:24.054 --> 23:26.709
The handprint
on the tree this morning.

23:26.840 --> 23:29.103
It was pollen dust from here.

23:29.233 --> 23:31.584
- You are getting better
at this, Paul.

23:31.714 --> 23:33.542
- Why would she
have us watched?

23:33.673 --> 23:36.719
- 'Cause we're nosing around,
getting closer to something.

23:36.850 --> 23:39.635
- Maite's been Council Chair
for ten years.

23:39.766 --> 23:41.855
Never wavered,
always led strong.

23:41.985 --> 23:44.074
- Before Strego got shot,
he said,

23:44.205 --> 23:47.295
"Where one world ends,
the next one begins."

23:47.426 --> 23:48.557
I know you don't want
to believe

23:48.688 --> 23:51.125
there are others
like Chill and Strego.

23:51.255 --> 23:53.301
Mooners who have stopped
believing in the Bridge.

23:53.432 --> 23:55.042
That--that somehow,
that's impossible.

23:55.172 --> 23:57.958
- It is impossible!
- Tell me why?

23:58.088 --> 23:59.960
Why would Mooners not want
to keep this

24:00.090 --> 24:02.179
all for themselves?

24:02.310 --> 24:04.486
Let alone risk their lives
to save a planet

24:04.617 --> 24:06.140
they've never even been to.

24:06.270 --> 24:09.273
- Because this isn't Earth.

24:09.404 --> 24:11.319
We don't take our lives
for granted.

24:11.450 --> 24:13.147
We're not looking for a--
a reason to run away

24:13.277 --> 24:15.236
or give up.

24:15.366 --> 24:17.194
Everything we do
is for the Bridge.

24:17.325 --> 24:21.460
It's not our job.
It's our purpose. Our promise.

24:21.590 --> 24:23.636
That's Truelune.

24:23.766 --> 24:25.638
We're not gonna get scared off.

24:25.768 --> 24:27.988
I don't think
you can understand it, Bella.

24:29.511 --> 24:31.382
- I've seen it happen.

24:31.513 --> 24:34.473
I've made it happen.

24:34.603 --> 24:37.388
Fear spreads like fire
once it starts.

24:38.912 --> 24:41.480
If someone wants you all
to burn,

24:41.610 --> 24:43.438
you will.

24:51.272 --> 24:54.231
[eerie music]

24:54.275 --> 25:01.108
♪

25:07.723 --> 25:09.769
[Thimbles trill]

25:12.859 --> 25:14.861
[IO whirring]

25:14.991 --> 25:17.777
[system trilling]

25:17.820 --> 25:24.697
♪

25:35.708 --> 25:38.493
[electronic thrumming]

25:52.899 --> 25:55.118
[IO trilling]

25:55.162 --> 26:02.125
♪

26:18.968 --> 26:21.841
[music intensifying]

26:21.884 --> 26:28.761
♪

26:42.949 --> 26:45.125
[IO trills]

26:48.432 --> 26:50.696
- Council Chair.

26:50.739 --> 26:56.310
♪

26:58.791 --> 27:00.053
Maite!

27:02.446 --> 27:03.970
- You're telling us
she gave you no reason

27:04.013 --> 27:04.884
for her decision?

27:05.014 --> 27:06.973
- She did not.

27:07.103 --> 27:08.583
- And without her consent,

27:08.714 --> 27:11.238
the transport ships cannot
enter Lune's atmosphere?

27:11.368 --> 27:14.502
- IO waits for both keys.

27:14.633 --> 27:16.069
- If the First Wave
is prevented

27:16.199 --> 27:17.766
from leaving on time,

27:17.897 --> 27:20.160
all Earth will know
something is wrong.

27:20.290 --> 27:22.858
- There will be
chaos, collapse.

27:25.165 --> 27:27.733
Those ships
must be allowed to land.

27:27.863 --> 27:29.604
- She has the will
of her people.

27:29.735 --> 27:31.562
I can't force her to act.

27:33.347 --> 27:35.436
- We buried the key
to our survival on the Moon

27:35.566 --> 27:37.090
for one reason.

27:37.220 --> 27:38.395
Because we could trust them

27:38.526 --> 27:40.136
more than we could trust
ourselves.

27:40.267 --> 27:43.096
What game are they playing at?

27:46.839 --> 27:49.842
[wind whistling]

27:49.972 --> 27:52.758
- You've all worked hard
these last few months.

27:52.888 --> 27:54.368
Hard enough to still be here

27:54.498 --> 27:57.676
and call yourselves
students of IO.

27:57.806 --> 27:59.808
Today, you will be given
a demonstration

27:59.939 --> 28:03.464
of just what it is
you're working toward.

28:03.594 --> 28:06.641
These poison pools bubble up
throughout the Lowlands,

28:06.772 --> 28:08.904
ensuring that nothing lives
or grows

28:09.035 --> 28:11.951
in nearly 2/3
of the United City States,

28:12.081 --> 28:15.650
a result of over half a century
of war and migration.

28:18.000 --> 28:20.350
Anyone thirsty?
[students groan]

28:20.481 --> 28:22.048
Now...
- No way.

28:22.178 --> 28:24.877
- Thanks to IO technology,

28:25.007 --> 28:28.184
built and working
on the Moon...

28:28.228 --> 28:31.100
[mysterious music]

28:31.144 --> 28:33.581
♪

28:33.712 --> 28:36.627
[electricity crackling]

28:36.671 --> 28:40.457
♪

28:40.588 --> 28:43.156
[students chatter excitedly]

28:43.286 --> 28:45.985
The purest water
you've ever seen.

28:46.115 --> 28:49.466
Built one molecule at a time.

28:49.597 --> 28:51.991
- It's clear!
[chuckles]

28:52.121 --> 28:53.166
- Drink up!

28:57.300 --> 29:00.129
Go ahead.
[students chatter]

29:00.173 --> 29:05.961
♪

29:06.092 --> 29:08.659
- The future is better.

29:08.790 --> 29:10.966
- You really think
they'll just let us have it?

29:11.097 --> 29:12.968
All of that great tech?

29:13.099 --> 29:14.927
- Who?
- People.

29:15.057 --> 29:18.408
The strong take what they want
and leave the rest to suffer.

29:18.539 --> 29:19.845
- [sighs]

29:19.975 --> 29:22.412
That's why IO was built
up there.

29:22.543 --> 29:25.851
Look at Moonhaven,
all they've accomplished.

29:25.981 --> 29:28.810
It's--
- Paradise, I know.

29:28.941 --> 29:31.204
One they get to live in
while we starve

29:31.334 --> 29:34.033
and suffer and burn down here.

29:34.163 --> 29:36.165
- It takes time.

29:36.296 --> 29:39.386
We can't just keep making
the world better for the few,

29:39.516 --> 29:40.648
for the powerful.

29:40.779 --> 29:42.911
- [sighs]
- It all has to change.

29:43.042 --> 29:44.565
Like ICON says,

29:44.695 --> 29:48.177
"Technology without culture
doesn't work."

29:48.308 --> 29:52.094
Moonhaven does.
They'll teach us.

29:52.225 --> 29:53.835
- You're gonna be
the Envoy, you know.

29:53.966 --> 29:55.750
The brilliant,
passionate orphan.

29:55.881 --> 29:57.621
People are already talking
about you.

29:57.752 --> 30:01.103
- If it's me,
I'll give it everything.

30:01.234 --> 30:02.409
I'll give it my life.

30:05.368 --> 30:06.892
- [sighs]

30:09.677 --> 30:12.593
[birds chirping]

30:18.729 --> 30:20.819
- Elna said
you wanted to see me.

30:25.911 --> 30:29.523
- I was sharp with you. Unfair.

30:29.653 --> 30:31.438
I offer 'pologies.

30:31.568 --> 30:32.787
And...

30:35.529 --> 30:36.704
A gift.

30:41.056 --> 30:43.929
Parts for your ship.
From a Maker.

30:44.059 --> 30:46.409
- [chuckles]
I know what they are.

30:48.368 --> 30:49.630
- I'm coming.

31:12.305 --> 31:14.133
- [grunts]

31:14.176 --> 31:17.136
[soft music]

31:17.179 --> 31:23.272
♪

31:23.403 --> 31:25.100
- Is it hard?

31:25.231 --> 31:26.754
- To learn.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.321
Once you do, it's easy.

31:31.890 --> 31:34.370
- Fingers remember.

31:34.501 --> 31:37.286
- You're a strange kid.

31:37.417 --> 31:38.766
- Grats.

31:40.942 --> 31:42.813
- [sighs]

31:42.944 --> 31:46.687
- I want to learn
more about you,

31:46.817 --> 31:49.908
what your life's like on Earth.

31:50.038 --> 31:52.736
- Hmm.
- When I first saw you,

31:52.867 --> 31:54.608
I had a feeling.

31:54.738 --> 31:57.437
We call it eyewarm,

31:57.567 --> 31:59.830
when you see someone

31:59.961 --> 32:02.442
and you think you know them,

32:02.572 --> 32:04.357
but you've never
seen them before.

32:06.794 --> 32:11.233
As a little,
I thought it was "eye worm."

32:11.364 --> 32:13.322
Like a worm crawled
into your eye

32:13.453 --> 32:15.020
and spoke you who to like.

32:15.150 --> 32:17.109
- You are
your father's daughter.

32:19.459 --> 32:22.679
I'm gonna need your help
threading this in.

32:22.810 --> 32:26.205
Uh-huh.
Just snap in the harness.

32:26.335 --> 32:27.902
And press your finger there

32:28.033 --> 32:29.948
till you feel it
lock into place.

32:30.078 --> 32:31.384
- Okay.

32:33.821 --> 32:37.781
- Sh--oh, shit. Sorry.

32:37.912 --> 32:39.435
- My mistake?

32:39.566 --> 32:42.177
- No, you're doing great.

32:42.308 --> 32:43.570
Here.

32:43.700 --> 32:46.355
Keep holding it. Beautiful.

32:46.399 --> 32:51.970
♪

32:52.100 --> 32:55.451
[engine thrums]

32:55.582 --> 32:58.846
- We did it.
Can she fly now?

33:03.068 --> 33:05.940
[engine whirring]

33:34.055 --> 33:37.537
- Oh, she wants to run.

33:37.667 --> 33:38.973
Should we let her?

33:41.715 --> 33:43.630
[engines thrum]

33:43.760 --> 33:46.024
This is my favorite part.

33:46.154 --> 33:48.374
- What?

33:48.504 --> 33:49.636
- The lag.

33:58.079 --> 34:00.299
[engine rumbling]

34:04.129 --> 34:06.696
- Shit!

34:06.827 --> 34:09.656
- [laughs]

34:11.310 --> 34:13.660
[engine droning distantly]

34:15.575 --> 34:17.707
- Elna.

34:17.751 --> 34:20.623
[awed music]

34:20.667 --> 34:27.326
♪

34:45.300 --> 34:48.434
- We made that.

34:48.564 --> 34:50.871
- Who did?

34:51.001 --> 34:52.525
- People.

34:56.094 --> 34:59.009
We can do anything.

34:59.053 --> 35:06.016
♪

35:26.298 --> 35:33.043
- ♪ I know a wish
is but a breath of air ♪

35:33.087 --> 35:37.091
♪ Blowing through my teeth

35:39.137 --> 35:45.143
♪ But if that breath
can make a change ♪

35:45.186 --> 35:51.758
♪ I'll wish again
for more belief ♪

35:54.152 --> 35:56.589
[sonic boom]

35:58.199 --> 36:01.115
[engine droning]

36:02.986 --> 36:05.250
Well, her life-plan is set.

36:05.380 --> 36:07.121
- [chuckles]
She could do worse.

36:09.167 --> 36:12.648
- Bella, do you know
why your mother came here?

36:12.779 --> 36:14.389
- There was a group
of 30 Earthers

36:14.520 --> 36:16.304
selected as a test.

36:16.435 --> 36:18.959
The first to go here
after the 80-year blackout.

36:20.265 --> 36:21.440
They called it a lottery,

36:21.570 --> 36:24.138
but you had to be
crazy qualified.

36:24.269 --> 36:27.446
- She was special.
- She was smart, I guess.

36:27.576 --> 36:29.665
I don't know
much more than that.

36:29.796 --> 36:31.450
We were living
in some kind of commune.

36:31.580 --> 36:33.103
I don't remember it.

36:34.801 --> 36:37.151
When you gave me
the parts to my ship,

36:37.282 --> 36:39.153
you must have considered
that I might leave.

36:41.199 --> 36:43.549
- I don't know
what you're up against,

36:43.679 --> 36:46.378
but if you're going to help me,
I want it to be your choice.

36:46.508 --> 36:47.640
[device chimes]

36:49.119 --> 36:50.512
- What?

36:50.643 --> 36:52.906
- Elna!

36:52.949 --> 36:55.909
[tense music]

36:55.952 --> 36:58.303
♪

36:58.433 --> 37:00.000
Blu sent word from here.

37:00.130 --> 37:01.610
- Blu!

37:01.741 --> 37:04.309
- [groans]
- Oh!

37:04.439 --> 37:06.528
Tell what happened.
Did Sirl do this to you?

37:06.659 --> 37:08.269
- [groaning]
He did.

37:08.400 --> 37:11.141
I followed him here.

37:11.272 --> 37:14.014
He was making for that cave
but glanced me in the trees.

37:14.144 --> 37:17.235
He came hard for me.
Meant to kill.

37:17.365 --> 37:18.932
- A goddamn kid.

37:18.975 --> 37:25.852
♪

37:32.902 --> 37:35.035
- I fought back.
- Yeah.

37:36.863 --> 37:38.343
- Violence is never
our first choice,

37:38.473 --> 37:41.433
but we will defend ourselves.

37:41.563 --> 37:43.348
- Doda!

37:43.391 --> 37:50.268
♪

37:55.621 --> 37:58.014
- Device for extracting
the Mark.

37:58.145 --> 37:59.494
Sirl's work.

38:01.801 --> 38:04.543
- Doda, look.

38:08.198 --> 38:10.113
So many.

38:10.244 --> 38:12.072
Why would people take them out?

38:13.552 --> 38:16.163
- Some of them are fresh.

38:16.206 --> 38:22.865
♪

38:29.611 --> 38:30.699
Paul.

38:32.484 --> 38:34.181
Paul!

38:34.312 --> 38:37.097
If Sirl told the others,
they'll come for Tomm.

38:37.227 --> 38:39.055
We need to get to Arlo.

38:39.099 --> 38:42.711
♪

38:42.755 --> 38:45.671
[ominous music]

38:45.714 --> 38:48.369
♪

38:48.500 --> 38:50.415
- What's all this?

38:50.545 --> 38:53.766
- Trouble comes.

38:53.896 --> 38:55.768
- He was walking
on the ceiling.

38:55.898 --> 38:58.205
[gasps]
The little one.

38:58.336 --> 39:00.076
- He's coming back
from the inbetween.

39:00.120 --> 39:05.299
♪

39:05.430 --> 39:08.041
- It's not safe for you here.

39:08.171 --> 39:11.218
- If they come for Tomm,
they come for me.

39:16.441 --> 39:18.921
- IO warned us.

39:19.052 --> 39:21.228
It predicted all of this.

39:21.359 --> 39:24.057
- You could have asked me.

39:24.187 --> 39:25.885
I would have warned you too.

39:29.410 --> 39:32.805
- Tomm will have answers
to all this when he wakes.

39:32.935 --> 39:35.634
What would you say
if you were him?

39:38.419 --> 39:41.814
- I'd say,
"I came upon the Earther pilot

39:41.944 --> 39:44.338
"conspiring
with the Mooner spy,

39:44.469 --> 39:46.340
and I tried to kill them both."

39:49.517 --> 39:50.779
- I don't think
you've come from Earth

39:50.910 --> 39:52.390
to destroy us.

39:54.609 --> 39:57.960
I looked hard into your past.

39:58.091 --> 40:01.224
I saw a broken girl

40:01.355 --> 40:03.313
who married a war

40:03.444 --> 40:06.404
and then spun away
into a life so small,

40:06.534 --> 40:09.929
gravity couldn't even find her.

40:10.059 --> 40:11.321
I don't think
you could care enough

40:11.452 --> 40:13.454
to make or destroy anything.

40:15.587 --> 40:17.371
I've met you before, Bella.

40:17.502 --> 40:20.330
I've met you a thousand times.

40:20.461 --> 40:23.464
The ones who only know
how to survive.

40:23.508 --> 40:26.467
[somber music]

40:26.511 --> 40:31.559
♪

40:31.690 --> 40:33.518
- I'll tell you a story.

40:37.391 --> 40:39.698
Our competition has arrived.

40:39.828 --> 40:43.179
- We don't have any.
- [chuckles]

40:44.529 --> 40:45.791
[explosion]
[screams]

40:45.921 --> 40:48.184
[gunshots]

40:48.315 --> 40:50.665
- We've gotta go.
I know a way out.

40:50.709 --> 40:52.188
[tense music]

40:52.319 --> 40:54.277
- They've come
to steal the tech.

40:54.408 --> 40:55.540
We can't let them take it.

40:55.670 --> 40:57.280
- There's nothing we can do.

40:57.324 --> 41:00.196
[screaming]

41:00.240 --> 41:04.549
♪

41:04.679 --> 41:06.246
- What now?

41:06.376 --> 41:09.205
[weapon whirring]
- [panting]

41:15.429 --> 41:17.431
- Let's go!

41:19.868 --> 41:22.741
- Come with us.
You'll be safe.

41:22.871 --> 41:24.917
- Us?

41:25.047 --> 41:26.658
You're one of them?

41:26.788 --> 41:29.574
- Basta, come on!

41:29.704 --> 41:32.315
- How could you do this?

41:32.446 --> 41:34.274
- [sighs]

41:37.625 --> 41:40.585
[pensive music]

41:40.628 --> 41:47.461
♪

41:55.077 --> 41:58.037
- [moans]

41:58.167 --> 42:00.387
How could you--
how could you...

42:00.518 --> 42:03.521
[panting]
Where am I?

42:03.651 --> 42:05.740
- He's coming to.
- Where am I?

42:05.871 --> 42:08.700
[insects chirping]

42:10.179 --> 42:11.964
[twigs snapping]

42:12.007 --> 42:14.923
[ominous music]

42:14.967 --> 42:16.882
♪

42:17.012 --> 42:18.927
- No!
[moans]

42:18.971 --> 42:25.804
♪

42:28.633 --> 42:30.765
♪

42:30.896 --> 42:32.680
Why won't you let
the ships land?

42:32.811 --> 42:35.117
I want to know it's safe.

42:35.248 --> 42:39.339
Humankind is fallible,
but IO is not.

42:39.469 --> 42:40.993
[Warbling]

42:41.123 --> 42:44.649
There's only a little to see
before the fight, but watch.

42:44.779 --> 42:46.912
Why would he kill her
for a flower?

42:47.042 --> 42:51.438
It's a trap! The Earthers will
kill us all when we land!

42:51.569 --> 42:53.135
Envoy,
what are you doing?

42:53.266 --> 42:54.484
[Silenced gunshot]No!

42:54.615 --> 42:58.010
♪
